comments: Milton (PHI) legally contests Jackson's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Batum (LAC) extends his right arm forward and is not in a legal guarding position when contact occurs with Harden's (PHI) front/left arm after Harden's gather.
Morris Sr. (LAC) turns slightly as he firms up over his left foot and he absorbs the side-to-side contact with Harris (PHI) during the screen.
Harris (PHI) is moving alongside Leonard's (LAC) path and maintains a rested forearm on Leonard's front when marginal contact occurs at the end of the drive.
Embiid (PHI) extends his left hand forward and initiates contact with Morris Sr.'s (LAC) front, affecting Morris Sr.'s SQBR as he starts his dribble.

George (LAC) jumps forward toward Harris (PHI) and marginal body contact occurs after Harris picks up his dribble in the backcourt. George then leans away from Harris prior to marginal contact occurring with Harris' front as he passes.
Jackson (LAC) brings his right hand toward Melton's (PHI) left side and marginal contact occurs as Melton elevates to pass.
George (LAC) and Harden (PHI) engage and disengage with one another after the expiration of the screen during the inbound.

Replay review of the foul called on Batum (LAC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Batum makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Embiid (PHI) prior to incidental contact occurring.

Replay review of the foul called on Melton (PHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Melton extends his right hand forward and initiates contact with George's (LAC) right elbow during his upward shooting motion.
Leonard (LAC) brushes Harden's (PHI) left wrist and marginal contact occurs as Harden crosses over.
George (LAC) and Embiid (PHI) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Leonard (LAC) and George (LAC) each legally contest Harden's (PHI) driving shot attempt.
Morris Sr. (LAC) brings his hands toward Embiid's (PHI) side and marginal contact occurs after the release of the shot attempt.

Embiid (PHI) brings his right arm forward as he pursues the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Leonard's (LAC) shoulder and head as he secures the ball. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Leonard (LAC) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two steps before elevating for the shot attempt.
After making initial contact with the ball without dislodging it, Milton (PHI) initiates contact with Leonard's (LAC) right arm and affects his driving shot attempt.
George (LAC) commits a take foul on Embiid (PHI).
Harden (PHI) brings his left arm forward and marginal contact occurs with Batum's (LAC) left arm prior to the hand-off.
Harden (PHI) legally contests George's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Jackson (LAC) maintains his left foot as his pivot along the baseline and his heel does not step out of bounds prior to when he releases the pass.
Harris (PHI) legally contests Morris Sr.'s (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Harden (PHI) releases his hands away from George's (LAC) back and marginal contact occurs as Harden pursues the rebound.
